President Joe Biden and President Emmanuel Macron of France held a conversation regarding the situation in Afghanistan. They expressed appreciation for the hard work of their personnel in Kabul who are involved in the evacuation of their citizens, Afghan allies, and other vulnerable individuals. The leaders emphasized the need for ongoing coordination among allies and democratic partners, both through multilateral platforms and in terms of providing humanitarian aid and support for refugees. They also welcomed the upcoming virtual G7 leaders' meeting, which will focus on coordinating efforts and discussing a unified strategy.